{
    "name": "Queen of Staves",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "A lone, lightly armored traveler carrying a walking staff, a queen of staves mixes spell power with whirling quarterstaff attacks."
        },
        {
            "name": "Esmerelda Darkshadow",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Those who think all elves are creatures of light and joy have not met Esmerelda. Dressing in dark colors with a temperament to match, Esmerelda believes she is doomed to a life of pain and gloom. Only when her enemies lie broken at her feet does she crack the slightest hint of a smile. Yet this dour disposition is not simply part of her nature\u2014as a young woman, Esmerelda was told by an oracle that she would bring ruin and destruction to everything she ever loved. Two days later, her wife-to-be was slain by orcs. Resolved to never love again, she paints herself gray with ash to symbolize the death she carries.<br/><br/><b>Combat Encounters</b>: Esmerelda travels the world alone, attacking those who trigger her mercurial temper (such as by not keeping their distance). Any sort of romantic proposition or prophecy magic sends her into a rage.<br/><br/><b>Roleplaying Suggestions</b>: All Esmerelda can talk about is the ultimate futility of life and the inevitability of death and decay."
        }
    ],
